Conclusion / Answer
- these strategies can reduce environmental costs, but only to a limited or moderate extent under rapid LEO expansion
- reusable rockets help, but rebound effect is a major limitation
- alternative propellants seem the strongest direct mitigation strategy
- satellite miniaturization is the most double-edged strategy

